(,AS YOU LIKE IT*).

Blow, blow, thou winter wind, Thou art not so unkind As man"s ingratitude ; Thy tooth it not so keen, Because thou art not seen, Although thy breath be rude.

Freeze, freeze, thou bitter sky, That dost not bite so nigh As benefits forgot: Though thou the waters warp, Thy sting is not so sharp As friend remember'd not.
